- 3 medium kohlrabies
- 80g Greek yoghurt
- 70g soured cream
- 50g thick double cream
- 1 small garlic clove crushed
- 1 1/2 tsp lemon juice
- 1 tbsp olive oil
- 2 tbsp finely shredded mint
- 1 tsp dried mint
- 20g baby watercress
1/4 tsp - sumac
salt and white pepper


Peel the kohlrabies, cut into 1.5 dice and put in a large mixin bowl. Set aside and make dressing. 
Put the yoghurt, sourced cream and double cream, garlic, lemon juice and olive oil in a medium bowl. 
Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt and a healthy grind of pepper and whisk well. 
Add the dressing to the kohlrabi, follwed by the fresh and dried mint and half the watercress. 
Gently stir and place on a serving dish. Dot the remaining watercress on top and sprinkle with the sumac. 
